meanings.definition: To earn more than (someone or something else)
meanings.sent1: She is outearning her brother by working extra hours.
meanings.sent2: The company is outearning its competitors due to its innovative products.
meanings.sent3: The squirrel is outearning the rabbit in collecting nuts for the winter.
meanings.sent4: The student is outearning the teacher in solving complex math problems.
meanings.sent5: Outearning others requires dedication and hard work.

meanings.definition: To make more money than (someone or something else)
meanings.sent1: He is outearning his previous job by taking on freelance projects.
meanings.sent2: The successful entrepreneur is outearning many established businesses in the industry.
meanings.sent3: The cat is outearning the dog by selling handmade toys.
meanings.sent4: Her online store is outearning the physical store, proving the power of e-commerce.
meanings.sent5: Outearning competitors can lead to financial success and stability.
